    title: 'GROUPS',
    body: '''Group counters have pictures of units on them and represent 1-6 units of the same type and technology level. Place a numeral marker underneath the Group counter to indicate the number of units in the Group. Units of the same type and technology may join and leave Groups as they choose at any time (as counters allow). Group counters have two sides -- the back side is used to hide the unit's type and combat information. Group counters and their numeral markers start with their identity hidden from other players and are only revealed in combat. Some Replicator (40.0) Group counters have a 1 in the upper-right corner to indicate that they have Tactics 1 technology (9.3).''',
